 rigor, “Come as You Are” delivers all of that and more. Whether you’re navigating your own sexuality, supporting a partner, or working in a health or counseling profession, this book offers valuable insights that can change how you think about desire and intimacy.</p>\n<p>Its empowering message—that you are exactly who you should be and that your sexual self is worthy of celebration—is a refreshing antidote to the confusion and stigma that still surround female sexuality today. Emily Nagoski invites us all to come as we are, with curiosity, compassion, and confidence.</p>",
